BBC Music Magazine (November 2013)

English | 106 Pages | PDF | 42 Mb


BBC Music Magazine is a must for anyone with a passion for classical music. Classical music connoisseurs and new enthusiast alike will enjoy the fascinating features and reviews of over 120 new works in every issue.

In this issue: The 20 greatest violinists of the recorded era; James Naughtie talks to Sakari Oramo, the new man at the helm of the BBC Symphony Orchestra; from Victoria to Verdi, Brahms to Britten, John Bridcut explores how composers have approached the task of remembering the dead in the Requiem; and Julian Haylock looks at the life and work of NiccolÃƒÂ² Paganini, the most devilishly talented violinist of all time.
